"The first female impersonator to visit Stockton in many moons opened a sprightly act this weekend . . . billed as 'America's foremore,' was added to the regular Venice show last night. 'Miss' Blair came to Stockton from six months at the Culyer Club in Hollywood. Other coast engagements included nine months in Seattle's Spinning Wheel and a year at the Nut Club in San Francisco. Blair has appeared on the Orpheum and Fanchon-Marco circuits and is under management of Arthur Butler, owner of Silver King, dog movie star."
